<auth0_security_guide>
<title>AUTH0 SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Auth0 is a widely adopted identity-as-a-service platform. Misconfigurations in Auth0 can lead to authentication bypass, account takeover, privilege escalation, and data exposure. Security testing must cover tenant settings, application configurations, rules/actions, and token handling.</critical>

<scope>
- Universal Login and custom login pages
- OAuth 2.0/OIDC flows (authorization code, implicit, PKCE)
- Rules, Actions, and Hooks (server-side customization)
- Management API and authentication API
- Social connections and enterprise federations
- Multi-factor authentication and passwordless
- Token validation and JWT handling
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Enumerate Auth0 tenant and application configurations via metadata endpoints.
2. Test OAuth 2.0/OIDC flows for redirect URI validation, state/nonce handling, and token leaks.
3. Probe rule/action logic for injection and bypass vulnerabilities.
4. Examine JWT tokens for algorithm confusion, claim manipulation, and validation gaps.
5. Test MFA enrollment and bypass scenarios.
</methodology>

